According to the azure documentation in this excellent article, they state that.
&ldquo;It&rsquo;s a good practice, and often a business requirement, to monitor web applications and back-end services, to ensure they&rsquo;re available and performing correctly. However, it&rsquo;s more difficult to monitor services running in the cloud than it is to monitor on-premises services.&rdquo;
&ldquo;There are many factors that affect cloud-hosted applications such as network latency, the performance, and availability of the underlying compute and storage systems and the network bandwidth between them.
